text:
According to a recent @ournetwork report on Onchain Social, OpenSocial, Farcaster, DSCVR, and Lens are the top4 onchain social protocols, with 250k+ combined daily active users.

- dscvr.one is new to me and is closely tied to Solana as a social network.
- opensocial.co may also be unfamiliar to many. It has raised $26M and recently partnered with BNB Chain to build a social graph and onchain identity.

The competition between "chains + social protocols" is heating up, with many chains seeing social graphs as key to their growth and aiming to make social protocols the foundation for their project communities.
https://www.ournetwork.xyz/p/on-268-onchain-social

text:
They say you're a product of the top 5 people you spend the most time with, but I think this also applies to parasocial relationships.

The more you read or listen to somebody online the more you start to sound like them too.

cast.text: I always think it‚Äôs interesting when people are remarkably similar in how they speak and sound. I told @matthew the other day he sounds just like Bezos. @dwr.eth and @fehrsam sound similar. Delian and Rabois. Zuck has a hint of Thiel. A buddy of mine sounds just like Rick Rubin. Feels like there‚Äôs something to it.
